 expressed as linear equations. In this context, there are two specific instances of objective functions provided: one is \\(15x + 12y\\), and another is \\(9a + 23b\\), where 'a' and 'b' represent the number of units of products A and B to be produced, respectively.\",3\n615,\"\"\"EXAMPLE OF LINEAR PROGRAMMING\"\"\",\"\"\"A company makes two products, cabinets and chests, which pass through carpentry and polishing departments. The time spent in each department and the available hours are given. The contribution to profit and fixed overheads is $100 for a cabinet and $150 for a chest. The optimal product mix to maximize total contribution to profit is calculated using linear programming.\"\"\",2\n1711,\"\"\"OPTIMUM PRODUCTION PLAN FOR LARGE APPLIANCES DIVISION\"\"\",\"\"\"The optimum production plan for the Large Appliances division is 240 units of Product F and 200 units of Product D, calculated using linear programming.\"\"\",1\n1712,\"\"\"QUIZ ON LINEAR PROGRAMMING AND LIMITING FACTORS\"\"\",\"\"\"This quiz involves questions on linear programming and limiting factors, including calculating contribution per unit of limiting factor, total contribution using simultaneous equations, and understanding shadow prices and slack values.\"\"\",1\n2139,\"\"\"OPTIMAL PRODUCTION STRATEGY FOR TABLET CO USING LINEAR PROGRAMMING\"\"\",\"\"\"Tablet Co makes two types of tablet computers, the Xeno (X) and the Yong (Y). The company uses linear programming to determine the optimal production plan to maximize contribution, considering constraints in build, program, and test stages.\"\"\",1\n2135,\"\"\"LINEAR PROGRAMMING FOR OPTIMAL PRODUCTION PLAN WITH RESOURCE CONSTRAINTS\"\"\",\"\"\"A company uses linear programming to establish an optimal production plan to maximize profit, considering constraints on materials and labor. The company must meet a minimum order requirement for one of its products while optimizing the use of limited resources.\"\"\",2\n2136,\"\"\"CONSTRAINT EQUATIONS